<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A newborn baby has been found wrapped in a plastic bag with stab wounds and a rusty knife protruding from her back.</p>

<p>The injured infant was found by a passerby on Costanera Oeste Avenue in the city of Posadas in the north-eastern Argentine province of Misiones.</p>

<p>Gym instructor Diego Sebastian Penayo, 31, found the baby wrapped in a blue and pink blanket and placed inside a black plastic bag.</p>

<p>A newborn baby (left and right) has been found wrapped in a plastic bag with stab wounds and a rusty knife protruding from her back</p>

<p>The infant had a knife sticking in her back but still displayed vital signs and was crying when Penayo passed by.</p>

<p>He took the baby to a nearby police station and she was later transferred to the Paediatric Hospital Dr. Fernando Barreyro for treatment.</p>

<p>Hospital doctors estimated that the baby was no older than two days and had multiple knife wounds on her body.</p>

<p>The baby was taken to a nearby police station and she was later transferred to the Paediatric Hospital Dr. Fernando Barreyro for treatment</p>

<p>News site Clarin said the rusty blade was still protruding from the tot's back.</p>

<p>Police reportedly identified the baby's mother and have arrested her.</p>

<p>Police told Clarin that the unnamed woman 'gave birth and left Hospital Dr. Ramon Madariaga Treble to go to a nearby street, where she abandoned the newborn girl'.</p>

<p>David Halac, a spokesperson for Hospital Dr. Fernando Barreyro, told the newspaper Cronica that the baby had a rusty knife made by the company Tramontina in her back along with several other injuries caused by the same blade.</p>

<p>Hospital workers have decided to call the baby Esperanza, meaning 'hope'. She is currently in a stable condition </p>

<p>He added: 'The baby is currently stable and we believe that she will survive.'</p>

<p>Halac said the stab wounds were mostly superficial and had not damaged any organs.</p>

<p>Hospital workers have decided to call the baby Esperanza, meaning 'hope'.</p>

<p>It is unclear whether the detained mother has been charged yet.</p>
